Cook,<br><br>
Don't know about any stats, per se. <br><br>
I believe you were in the 3rd Marines? You may try a net search in order to locate the 3rd or some of the other Marine unit's web pages.<br><br>
From there you may be able to find *morning reports* or *lessons learned* (don't know what they were called in the marines). Unit historians have a lot of this stuff and will make it available for guys trying to prove service related injuries or to substantiate PTSD claims.<br><br>
I received the Americal lessons learned for the entire time I was in Vietnam and found that my memory and recollection was right on for the most part. It was very interesting reading. You could probably compile your own stats - depending on how complete the reports were.<br><br>

